In December 2019, a cluster of patients in Wuhan, Hubei Province, China, presented with severe atypical pneumonia, and experts named the illness coronavirus disease 2019 (COVID-19; 
 European Centre for Disease Prevention and Control, 2020). Although the source of this viral outbreak remains elusive, the original 27 cases were linked to Southern Chinaâ€™s Wuhan Seafood Wholesale Market (
 European Centre for Disease Prevention and Control, 2020). This market is known for selling various bushmeat and other wild animals to the public for consumption, which was speculated to include an unidentified intermediate host for COVID-19. As in SARS-CoV, bats are understood to be the main host of the COVID-19 virus.
